   14-16, 2000},
Organization = {Wessex inst Technol; Univ Udine},
Abstract = {GolMexSur, a metadatabase for the oceanographic and meteorological
   information of the southern Gulf of Mexico (SGM) (17N 85W - 26N 99W) was
   designed and implemented in order to organize and manage in a fine and
   regular mesh, oceanic and meteorological data coming from several
   heterogeneous gross-grid-sized or sparse data sources. The metadatabase
   has three organizational components: (1) knowledge base, (2) metadata,
   and (3) data values. Knowledge base component contains three classes of
   knowledge: operating knowledge (triggers, processes, and integrity
   constraints), control knowledge for sequential systems interactions, and
   decision knowledge for parallel systems interactions. Metadata component
   contains organizational information related to the environmental and
   hydrological data: data's spatial and temporal location, measurement
   units, obtaining method, quality, etc. Finally, data values component
   represents the numerical value of each variable or parameter (sea
   surface temperature, wind speed, wind direction, sea level pressure,
   etc). Additionally, metadata and data values components have two
   temporal scopes: recent information, and historical information.
   GolMexSur has information from sources such as coastal airports, coastal
   meteorological stations, oceanographic cruises, buoys, wave gauges, and
   information derived or estimated from satellite imageries or numerical
   models. In a first stage, GolMexSur was designed and implemented using
   MS Visual FoxPro(@), but recently the design was modified to work with
   Oracle(@). The implementation of this metadatabase represents the first
   step of a major project, whose main objective is to build a regional
   operational oceanographic system for the SGM, and at present it is being
   used in studying the oceanic and atmospheric conditions in the SGM oil
   region.},
